Grafana installation
$sudo su
$wget https://dl.grafana.com/enterprise/release/grafana-enterprise-11.1.4.linux-amd64.tar.gz
$ls
$tar -zxvf grafana-enterprise-11.1.4.linux-amd64.tar.gz
tar: unzipping the file
tar command options:
z: using gzip
x: extract the file
v: verbose
f: followed by name of the file that u want to unzip

$ls
$cd Grafana-11.1.4
$./bin/grafana-server
Grafana works on port 3000……so in security group if port 3000 is enabled or not
Access grafana in web browser: <public_ip>:3000
Default username and password: admin
Setup docker server machine: Target
Another ec2 machine
$sudo su
$apt-get update -y
$apt install docker.io -y
$service docker start
$docker run -it --name c01 ubuntu
$docker run -it --name c02 ubuntu

PROMETHEUS INSTALLATION

$wget https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/releases/download/v2.53.2/prometheus-2.53.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
$tar -zxvf prometheus-2.53.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
We need to tell docker and Prometheus which httpd endpoint Prometheus would be reading/scraping
Docker needs to expose httpd endpoint
$vi /etc/docker/daemon.json
daemon.json: configuration file
Docker -> publishes it metrics on port 9232
Experimental: true

Allowing the use of experimental features

Metrics-addr: specify port where docker metrics endpoints would be exposed
$service docker restart
35.171.163.101:9323/metrics
Published metrics…
Tell Prometheus which endpoint to read
Prometheus.yaml -> it all the configuration of Prometheus
In this file we need to specify which httpd endpoint the Prometheus needs to scrape
$vi prometheus.yaml
Run the Prometheus
$./prometheus
Now open
<public_ip>:9090
